{"id":87252,"title":"[Postoperative complications in patients with cervicothoracic injuries].","abstract":"The results of the diagnosis and treatment of 117 patients with cervicothoracic injuries were analyzed. Different complications were observed in 51 (43.6%) cases. The main reasons contributing to the development of complications included late diagnosis of lesions of trachea and esophagus, acute blood loss, inadequate hemostasis during surgery. ","date":"2014-12-08","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25484145","annotations":[{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.762559,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.728515,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.705583,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Vertebrate trachea","weight":0.696645,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertebrate_trachea"},{"name":"Esophagus","weight":0.632853,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esophagus"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.595494,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Bleeding","weight":0.579861,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bleeding"},{"name":"Blood","weight":0.487247,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood"},{"name":"Acute (medicine)","weight":0.302155,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acute_(medicine)"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.298818,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Hemostasis","weight":0.0274275,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hemostasis"},{"name":"Developmental biology","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developmental_biology"}]}
